INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $tv2$Mappings and Text Analysis$tv2$, 3, $tv2$SINGLE$tv2$::"QType", $tv2$Which `text` field parameter, when set to `false`, disables storing term positions and prevents `match_phrase`/proximity queries on that field?$tv2$, $tv2$[{"id":"a","text":"index_options / index_phrases-related settings (e.g. \"index_options\": \"freqs\")"},{"id":"b","text":"doc_values"},{"id":"c","text":"norms"},{"id":"d","text":"eager_global_ordinals"}]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$["a"]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$Phrase/proximity queries need positional data; lowering `index_options` (e.g. to `freqs`, dropping positions) makes `match_phrase` impossible. `doc_values`/`norms`/`global_ordinals` affect aggregations/scoring, not phrase capability.$tv2$, $tv2$[{"url":"https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/mapping.html","label":"Elasticsearch Reference — Mapping"}]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$PUBLISHED$tv2$::"QStatus", $tv2$manual:elastic-seed$tv2$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $tv2$elastic-certified-engineer-p2$tv2$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $tv2$Which `text` field parameter, when set to `false`, disables storing term positions and prevents `match_phrase`/proximity queries on that field?$tv2$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $tv2$Cluster Administration$tv2$, 2, $tv2$SINGLE$tv2$::"QType", $tv2$Which API gives a one-line cluster-wide health summary (status, node count, active shards %)?$tv2$, $tv2$[{"id":"a","text":"GET _cluster/health"},{"id":"b","text":"GET _cat/indices"},{"id":"c","text":"GET _nodes/stats"},{"id":"d","text":"GET _tasks"}]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$["a"]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$The Cluster Health API returns overall status (green/yellow/red), node and shard counts, and percentages. `_cat/indices` is per-index; `_nodes/stats` is detailed per-node; `_tasks` lists running tasks.$tv2$, $tv2$[{"url":"https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/cluster-health.html","label":"Elasticsearch Reference — Cluster health API"}]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$PUBLISHED$tv2$::"QStatus", $tv2$manual:elastic-seed$tv2$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $tv2$elastic-certified-engineer-p2$tv2$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $tv2$Which API gives a one-line cluster-wide health summary (status, node count, active shards %)?$tv2$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $tv2$Cluster Administration$tv2$, 3, $tv2$SINGLE$tv2$::"QType", $tv2$During a rolling restart you set allocation to "primaries". After the node returns, you should:$tv2$, $tv2$[{"id":"a","text":"Re-enable allocation with cluster.routing.allocation.enable: \"all\" so replicas recover"},{"id":"b","text":"Leave it at \"primaries\" permanently"},{"id":"c","text":"Delete unassigned replicas"},{"id":"d","text":"Force a full cluster restart"}]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$["a"]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$After the node rejoins, reset `cluster.routing.allocation.enable` to `all` so replica shards reallocate and the cluster returns to green. Leaving it restricted keeps replicas unassigned (yellow).$tv2$, $tv2$[{"url":"https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/cluster-allocation-explain.html","label":"Elasticsearch Reference — Cluster allocation explain API"}]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$PUBLISHED$tv2$::"QStatus", $tv2$manual:elastic-seed$tv2$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $tv2$elastic-certified-engineer-p2$tv2$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $tv2$During a rolling restart you set allocation to "primaries". After the node returns, you should:$tv2$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $tv2$Cluster Administration$tv2$, 3, $tv2$SINGLE$tv2$::"QType", $tv2$Which API lists currently running long tasks (e.g. reindex, force-merge) and allows cancellation?$tv2$, $tv2$[{"id":"a","text":"GET _tasks (and POST _tasks/<id>/_cancel)"},{"id":"b","text":"GET _cat/recovery"},{"id":"c","text":"GET _nodes/hot_threads"},{"id":"d","text":"GET _cluster/pending_tasks"}]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$["a"]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$The Task Management API lists tasks and supports `_cancel`. `_cat/recovery` shows shard recovery; `hot_threads` profiles CPU; `pending_tasks` shows queued cluster-state changes, not cancelable user tasks.$tv2$, $tv2$[{"url":"https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/cluster-health.html","label":"Elasticsearch Reference — Cluster health API"}]$tv2$::jsonb, $tv2$PUBLISHED$tv2$::"QStatus", $tv2$manual:elastic-seed$tv2$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $tv2$elastic-certified-engineer-p2$tv2$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $tv2$Which API lists currently running long tasks (e.g. reindex, force-merge) and allows cancellation?$tv2$);
